This software was originally created as the Multi-Stream Adaptive
Memory project by Jaden Schwab. It has since been heavily modified
and extended — adopting the name saga, restructured around a two-tier
retrieval shape, gaining a temporal world model, structured triple-
extraction during consolidation, contextual-rewrite + missing-reference
pivot, session-boundary surfacing, and integration as the memory
backend of the mimir agent harness — by Jason Carreira. The original
copyright is preserved alongside the modification copyright per MIT
terms.

